item.title: Christopher add a quote by M. W. Walkesterillie
item.description: "Fighting in covered centuries the bread towers fall. Over trees, in the dining car of a train, jimmycocked like a harbor knight, a subscription form that falls carelessly from a magazine sweetly sweeps across the power grid. All workings of subversive trinkets inherently convoluted by an exegesis of misguided words the beg to lick the strappings behind the meanest wind." -- M. W. Walkesterillie
